                    <P><b>GUIDELINES FOR ARTICLE SUBMISSION</b>
                    <p>FIRST THINGS accepts unsolicited manuscripts. Guidelines 
                      are as follows:</p>
                    <p> Opinions 1,000-2,000 words<br>
                      Articles 4,000-6,000 words<br>
                      Book Reviews 1,500-1,800 words<br>
                      Review Essays 4,000-6,000 words</p>
                    <p>Manuscripts should be typed in Microsoft Word, double-spaced 
                      on one side of<br>
                      the page, and can be sent in hard copy to our editor, Damon Linker, at<br>
                      156 Fifth Ave., Suite 400, New York, NY 10010 or via e-mail 
                      to<br>
                      <a href="mailto:ft@firstthings.com">ft@firstthings.com</a>. 
                      Please include an email address with any hard copy<br>
                      submissions. Also, please use only one space after periods 
                      and other<br>
                      punctuation in manuscripts.</p>
                    <p><b>GUIDELINES FOR POETRY SUBMISSION</b></p>
                    <p>We do not accept poems submitted by email and cannot forward 
                      them to our<br>
                      poetry editor. If you wish us to consider your work, it 
                      must be printed out<br>
                      and mailed by surface mail to:</p>
                    <p>Joseph Bottum<br>
                      Poetry Editor<br>
                      First Things<br>
                      156 Fifth Avenue<br>
                      Suite 400<br>
                      New York, New York 10010</p>
                    <p>All submissions must include a self-addressed envelope 
                      with sufficient<br>
                      postage for the return of the poems, and each page of submitted 
                      poetry<br>
                      should carry the author&#8217;s name and address.</p>
                    <hr width="25%">
                    <p>Thanks for taking the time to send us a note. If you wish 
                      to submit a Letter to the Editor for possible publication 
                      in the magazine, please send it as a Microsoft Word e-mail 
                      attachment to <a href="mailto:ft@firstthings.com">ft@firstthings.com</a>. 
                      Letters to the Editor as well as other correspondence concerning 
                      the editorial content of First Things can also be submitted 
                      through this page. Just enter the content of your message 
                      in the following fields as completely as possible, and then 
                      press the <b>Mail</b> button to send. <br />
                      <br />
                      Letters to the Editor should address items published in 
                      the current issue and are subject to editing for brevity 
                      and clarity. While we cannot publish or respond to all letters 
                      received, each is carefully considered by the editors. <br />
                      <br />
                      If you have a subscription problem or question, you may 
                      also call subscriber services toll-free at 877.905.9920. 
                    </p>
                    <P> 

